<HEADLINE> Cross-Straits Cultural Camp In Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- More than 50 young scholars and
professors from Taiwan are involved in exchanges at a cultural
research camp from August 5 to 15 in north China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
During the ten-day event, the participants will discuss
cultural developments with their counterparts in Shanxi
during three historical periods: the Western Jin Dynasty
(265-316), Eastern Jin Dynasty (317-420) and the Later Jin
(936-946).
</P>
<P>
The camp is sponsored by the Taiwan Affairs Office of Shanxi
and a local cultural research association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
