<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast Kills Four in Pakistan-Held Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 8 (Xinhua) -- At least four people of a
family were killed and two others injured in a bomb blast in
GujarBandi, 56 kilometers from Muzaffarabad, capital of
Pakistan-held Kashmir, according to a report by Radio Pakistan
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The area is near the Line of Control, where for the last 10
days Pakistan and India were engaged in their worst ever border
firing.
</P>
<P>
The radio report said that the injured in Saturday's bomb blast
were shifted to a nearby hospital. The investigation is now
underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
