<HEADLINE> India Condemns Bomb Blasts in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister Atal
Bihari Vajpayee condemned Saturday the wanton acts of terrorism
perpetrated Friday in Nairobi and Dar es Salaam leading to tragic
loss of life, injuries to innocent people and widespread damage to
property.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of External Affairs said here that Vajpayee had
send a message to the presidents of Kenya, Tanzania and the United
States expressing deep shock and sorrow over the incidents.
</P>
<P>
A Spokesman for the External Affairs Ministry said Friday night
that India has always strongly condemned such acts of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that four staff members of the
Indian High Commission in Nairobi and four children of Indian
origin were among the thousands injured in the blast in the Kenyan
capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
