<HEADLINE>   Situation on Sino-Vietnamese Border Normal, Vietnam Affirms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's Foreign Ministry has
denied foreign newspaper reports about "abnormal" occurrences on
the border with China.
</P>
<P>
"The situation on the Sino-Vietnamese border area has of late
been normal," a spokesperson for the ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the stories in foreign newspapers were
untrue and were carried with ill intention.
</P>
<P>
"In fact, the Vietnam-China relationship has developed
fruitfully", the spokesperson said.
</P>
<P>
He added that progress had been made in negotiations on borders
between the two countries, which aimed to solve border issues
and define the delineation of the Beibu Gulf before the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson reaffirmed Vietnam's "unchanged policy of
developing good neighborliness and cooperation for mutual benefit
with China". 
</P>
</TEXT>
