<HEADLINE> 11 Killed by Rebels in N. Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed
Saturday in a pre-dawn attack by armed Hutu rebels known as
Interahamwe militia in Kanama commune, north Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
The attack by the militiamen armed with guns and traditional
weapons targeted Gatovu settlement where some local residents who
had dissociated themselves from the militias, the Rwanda News
Agency (RNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
"Eleven people were killed, while seven others were wounded,"
a senior army officer told RNA. The attack was carried out at
2:00 a.m (12:00 a.m) Saturday morning, the officer indicated.
</P>
<P>
The victims were hacked to death with clubs, machetes, and
other traditional weapons, the RNA said, in a dispatch to Xinhua
based here in Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
Security forces in the area were alerted, and repulsed the
attackers who vanished in the surrounding hills and banana
plantations.
</P>
<P>
According to the military sources in Gisenyi, north Rwanda,
the army carried out military operations Thursday in Kanama
commune, in which 38 Hutu militiamen were killed.
</P>
<P>
The renewed attacks by the Hutu militia follows Rwandan army's
crash on the insurgents in Gisenyi and Ruhengeri prefectures in
which many of their top commanders were killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
