<HEADLINE> Tehran Stock Exchange Index Falls Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The general price index at Tehran
Stock exchange dropped by 17.00 points Saturday to close at
1518.94 points.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,712,245 shares changed hands in 605 deals and the
turnover was 4.59 billion rials (about 820,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
There were 17 gaining issues and eight decliners.
</P>
<P>
The slump came after a central bank official announced that the
country would face a foreign exchange deficit of about 3.5 billion
dollars in the current Iranian year (ended in March 21, 1999) due
to a fall in oil revenues.
</P>
<P>
The black money market also reacted quickly. Informed sources
said the greenback climbed to about 5,600 rials Saturday from
5,570 a week ago.
</P>
<P>
It was only on Sunday that President Mohammad Khatami announced
the government would keep the official rate of 3,000 rials against
a dollar through this Iranian year. 
</P>
