various degrees, said the statement which went on to warn people
to keep away from those unsafe areas.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers have dugged out 11 corpses in the rubble since
Saturday afternoon and another two are proved to be alive but
still trapped deeply inside.
</P>
<P>
The government has allocated 50 million Shillings (some
850,000 U.S. Dollars) as the emergency fund for the tragedy,
according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement condemned the bomb attack, saying it broke out
without any warnings in advance.
</P>
<P>
A c-130 aircraft carrying 44 U.S. personnel with medical
supplies, food and communications equipment landed early
Saturday, while a c-1241 touched down shortly after 9.00 a.m.
with more medical equipment, said U.S. Air Force Major Neal
Kringel.
</P>
<P>
A British assistance team will arrive here Sunday to help the
government deal with the blast, the statement said. 
