carry out its investigations and also try to give a chance for
peace," said Bizimungu.
</P>
<P>
The Rwandan president joined his wife here and flew back to
his country. He arrived in Zambia Wednesday for a three-day state
visit and left for Zimbabwe with Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba for the regional summit Friday.
</P>
<P>
Seven presidents from Zimbabwe, Zambia, Tanzania, Namibia,
Rwanda and Uganda as well as the DRC attended the summit and they
have agreed that the on-going war in DRC must end and urged those
involved to lay down their arms.
</P>
<P>
However, political analysts said in the Victoria Falls that
there is no sign of a breakthrough and that the confrontation
between Kabila and his former backers is likely to continue.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here Saturday said troops loyal to Kabila
have launched a counter-attack in the west on the strategic river
corridor linking the capital Kinshasa to the sea. 
