<HEADLINE> Canada Urges Nevis Not to Secede From Federation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The government of Canada Saturday
called on the citizens of the Caribbean island of Nevis not to
vote to secede from their federation with Saint Kitts.
</P>
<P>
The Nevis Administration is preparing to hold a public
referendum on August 10, the ultimate result of which could be the
secession of Nevis from the two-island federation of Saint Kitts
and Nevis, if the threshold of at least two thirds of all valid
votes is met, as required by the constitution of Saint Kitts and
Nevis.
</P>
<P>
"As a friend of the Caribbean Community and Common Market,
Canada has been closely watching developments in the Caribbean
state of Saint Kitts and Nevis," said Foreign Affairs Minister
Lloyd Axworthy in a release published Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Canada firmly believes that in this age of global integration,
strength in all regions of the world is born of unity and closer
cooperation, not division and fragmentation," he added.
</P>
<P>
The government of Canada supports initiatives by the
populations and governments of Saint Kitts and Nevis to resolve
political differences through democratic processes based on the
rule of law, and strongly encourages ongoing efforts to find legal
alternatives to secession by Nevis, said the release. 
</P>
</TEXT>
