<HEADLINE> Heat Wave Hits Cyprus, Hundreds Hospitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The hospitals' emergency units
were on alert Saturday as Cyprus experienced the recorded hottest
day, with temperature soaring to 43 Celsius.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus News Agency said hundreds of people have been sent
to hospital after suffering dizziness, headache, heat stroke
symptoms and dehydration.
</P>
<P>
According to the Meteorological Service, the temperature is
four degrees higher than usual and the heat wave will last till
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus last month witnessed the second hottest July over the
past 60 years, with an average maximum daily temperature of 38.4
Celsius.
</P>
<P>
Cyrpus' hottest July was in 1978, with average maximum daily
temperature reaching 39 Celsius, the service said. 
</P>
