<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, August 9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The hijacking of a Russian TU-154 aircraft hijacked
Sunday ended peacefully with 97 passengers released unharmed. The
Interior Ministry department based in the local Domodedovo airport
said that no explosives were found on the plane.
</P>
<P>
All the passengers who took the Irkutsk-Tyumen-Moscow flight
are now out of danger in the airport's VIP lounge, the Interfax
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Federal Security Service (FSB) servicemen, however, are
searching and questioning the passengers to identify the author of
hand-written note that threatened to blow up the aircraft unless
100,000 U.S. dollars was provided.
</P>
<P>
The handwriting of each passenger is being compared with the
note to trace down the terrorist who is obviously among the
passengers. (Russia-Hijack-End)
</P>
