<HEADLINE> Dalian Tops Chinese Soccer League (Updated) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- An under-strength Dalian Wanda
overcame lowly Wuhan Hongjinlong 1-0 to remain runaway leader in
the Chinese first division soccer league on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The defending champion, which benched star defenders Zhang
Enhua and Sun Jihai and defensive midfielder Li Ming, scored the
winning goal through Czech Vaclav Nemecek in the 55th minute of
the 17th round game.
</P>
<P>
Wanda head coach Xu Gengbao said he hadn't expected such a
tough game.
</P>
<P>
Qi Wusheng, former head coach of the Chinese national team who
took the helm of Hongjinlong last week, admitted the gap between
his team and Wanda was wide.
</P>
<P>
"Anyway, I'm satisfied with my team's performance," Qi said.
</P>
<P>
Wanda has collected 39 points with a record of 12 wins, three
draws and two losses, seven points over second-placed former
champion Shanghai Shenhua, which routed Sichuan Quanxing 4-1 on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Shenhua has lost only one game but drawn eight.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Guo'an squandered a 2-0 halftime lead, tying host
Taishan Luneng 3-3.
</P>
<P>
Luneng scored three goals within 12 minutes in early second
half to snatch the lead. Guo'an's veteran Hu Jianping scored his
second goal to make it 3-3.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other games, Shenyang Haishi edged Qingdao Hainiu
1-0, Chinese Army drew Shenzhen Ping'an 1-1, Guangzhou Songri
beats Guangzhou Apollo 3-1 and Vanguards Huandao downed Yanbian
Aodong 2-1. 
</P>
