<HEADLINE> Third Tropical Storm Nears South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The third tropical storm of the
year was forming over the eastern South China Sea this morning and
is expected to hit south China's Guangdong Province by Monday
afternoon or evening.
</P>
<P>
The center of the storm is moving in a northwesterly direction
at a speed of 20 kilometers an hour, according to reports from the
Central Meteorological Administration.
</P>
<P>
Coastal areas of Guangdong can expect strong breezes to
moderate gales tonight. 
</P>
