<HEADLINE> Blue-Chip Stock Regulation Agreement Reached </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The first group of 30 blue chip
stocks listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchanges reached an agreement
with the exchanges today on the regulation of information
disclosure.
</P>
<P>
These are the stocks of large enterprises which have enjoyed
good economic performances and have great potential for
development.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached in accordance with related laws,
forbidding the concerned parties from insider trading and
publicizing unauthorized information.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also requires them to make timely replies to
questions raised by the Shanghai Stock Exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is aimed at making listed corporations meet their
obligation to provide accurate and timely information in order to
guarantee their smooth development, said Tu Guangshao, general
manager of the Shanghai Stock Exchanges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
