<HEADLINE> Bulgarians Holds Memorial Meeting for Zhivkov </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Approximately 10,000 people
gathered in central Sofia Sunday for a memorial meeting to pay
their last respects to former Bulgarian Communist Party leader
Todor Zhivkov who died last week.
</P>
<P>
The memorial meeting, held in the Battenberg square, started
with the play of the Bulgarian national anthem while Zhivkov's
body lay in state. The meeting was organized by Zhivkov's
relatives and the Bulgarian Socialist Party (BSP).
</P>
<P>
Zhivkov died last Wednesday in a Sofia hospital at the age of
86.
</P>
<P>
Zhivkov was in power for 35 years from 1954 until 1989 when he
lost power and was expelled from the Bulgarian Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
After the memorial meeting, about 5,000 people escorted the
hearse to the Central Cemetery in Sofia, where Zhivkov's body was
buried in the same grave with his wife, Mara Maleeva, who died
earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
