<HEADLINE> Lucent, Unicom Reach Agreement on GSM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The Lucent Technology Ltd.
Co. of the United States reached an agreement with China's United
Telecommunication Corporation (Unicom) today on the joint
launching of the GSM (Global System for Mobile Phones) project in
12 cities of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 27 million U.S. dollars, the U.S.
side will offer equipment while the Chinese side provides funding
for the project, which will have 245,000 lines and enable people
to use mobile telephones in all parts of the province after
completion.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation on the GSM project is the first of its kind since
Lucent began doing business in China, said Bandy Yeh, vice-
president of the U.S. corporation.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of China has invested 1.5 billion yuan (about 190
million U.S. dollars) in loans in Unicom's Liaoning GSM project.
The project was launched last year with a projected scale of
313,000 lines, and Lucent will join Unicom to complete the
remaining part of the project.
</P>
<P>
After completion, the GSM network will make mobile telephones
accessible everywhere in Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The Lucent company gained the project through public bidding
early this year, and will now team with Unicom, a large
state-owned telecommunication corporation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
