<HEADLINE> Iranian President Calls for Islamic Unity Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami Sunday called on the Islamic countries to close their
ranks to confront the Israeli expansionist policies, Tehran radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
Receiving visiting Jordanian Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign
Minister Jawad Anani, Khatami termed Israel as the biggest enemy
of Islam and the mankind, saying unity among Islamic nations is
the only way to confront the Israeli expansion.
</P>
<P>
He expressed concern over the establishment of Israeli bases
in the region, saying that "national interests oblige us to
confront the Israeli expansion more seriously."
</P>
<P>
Terming the Islamic countries as the strongest and richest
nations from the points of cultural heritage, suitable geographic
positions and rich natural resources, Khatami said these
advantages should be explored for solidarity among the Islamic
countries.
</P>
<P>
He expressed regret over the current situation of Muslims in
the world, saying that massacres, killings and robberies are still
seen in Afghanistan and "what more concerns us is that all of
these things happened under the name of Islam."
</P>
<P>
Underlining the need of unity and solidarity among Muslim
nations, he said that the Islamic countries should cooperate with
each other in the path of development.
</P>
<P>
Anani, who arrived here Saturday and handed over a written
message from King Hussein to Khatami, voiced his country's
readiness to expand relations with Iran.
</P>
<P>
Jordan attaches importance to friendly, good and lasting
contacts with Iran, Anani said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
