<HEADLINE> Kunming Trade Fair Attracts Large Domestic Investments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The ongoing 1998 Kunming Export
Commodities Trade Fair has attracted 1.68 billion yuan of domestic
investment to southwest China's Yunnan Province, marking a
successful domestic contribution to the fair.
</P>
<P>
Those investments are primarily in the fields of tourism,
minerals, medicine and biological exploration.
</P>
<P>
The fair, approved by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation and jointly sponsored by seven provinces,
cities and autonomous regions in south and southwest China, is a
regional export commodities trade fair which aims to tap the
southeast Asia market.
</P>
<P>
Since it began five years ago, the fair has cemented deals
worth a total of more than 7 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
This year, the fair has especially intensified its efforts to
attract domestic businessmen, and to date this move has appeared
to pay off as more than 300 businesses from all over China are
attending the the fair. 
</P>
