<HEADLINE> PLA Sends More Men and Materials to Flooded Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The General Logistics Department
of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) and Railway
Departments this afternoon sent an additional 41 trains loaded
with 20,000 soldiers and relief materials to flood-ravaged areas.
</P>
<P>
Another 25 trains will soon set off from Beijing, Jinan,
Chengdu and three other cities for the front lines of the flood
fighting effort.
</P>
<P>
In the past five days, the PLA has dispatched 134 motor
vehicles, 300 tents, 165 tons of food and 10,000 life-preservers
to flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
At present, more than 10,000 officers and soldiers are on red
alert on the Yangtze River dikes, which is facing an attack from
the fourth flood crest.
</P>
<P>
Some 7,500 PLA men built a 2,000-meter--long secondary dike at
Dongting Lake today as the water level at the Chenglingji
measuring site rose to 35.57 meters, the fourth highest level of
the year.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,500 armed policemen have repaired 200 danger spots along
the Hannan embankment, which serves to protect the large central
China industrial city of Wuhan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
