<HEADLINE> India Threatens to Reclaim Areas Under Pakistan Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Indian Defense Minister George
Fernandes Sunday threatened to reclaim areas in Jammu and Kashmir
which are now under Pakistani control, and ruled out conversion of
the line of control in the disputed region into an international
border.
</P>
<P>
"There is a part of Jammu and Kashmir which is occupied by
Pakistan, and that part has to be reclaimed," Fernandes told the
local Eenadu TV.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether the line of control in Jammu and Kashmir should
be converted into an international border between India and
Pakistan based on the ground realities, Fernandes said: "That is
not the position of the government and I don't think that will be
the position of the government (in future also)."
</P>
<P>
The Indian minister also said his government had planned
special measures which were in the process of being implemented in
Kashmir. He did not elaborate. 
