<HEADLINE> China to Offer More Support for High-Tech Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
said here today that the central government has decided to give
more support and adopt more effective measures for development of
high-tech ventures.
</P>
<P>
Li also called for the early establishment of a risk investment
system for high-tech ventures and the listing of profitable
high-tech ventures.
</P>
<P>
Li, also member of the the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, said here today at the
closing session of a national conference on high technology
development zones, that the 21st century will be a knowledge
economy era during which high-tech is expected to become a pillar
industry, and future economic growth will depend on high
technology.
</P>
<P>
Li said the the development of high-tech ventures should cater
to the needs of the economic growth and help enhance national
economic competitive capability.
</P>
<P>
Li urged the industrialization of more high-tech programs which
are believed to create more job opportunities for the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
The Vice-Premier also said he expects high technology to help
upgrade state-owned ventures and lead the development of the entire
economy.
</P>
<P>
This morning, Li visited a national high-tech development fair
which is displaying China's achievements in this field during the
past 10 years.
</P>
<P>
China has so far established 53 high technology development
zones and high-tech ventures have provided job opportunities for
at least 2.87 million Chinese people.  
</P>
