<HEADLINE> Economic Growth Helps Healthy Development of Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Tu Guangshao, general manager of
the Shanghai Stock Exchange, said here today that China's stable
economic growth is of the greatest importance to the healthy
development of the country's stock market during the Asian
financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a ceremony at which the Shanghai Stock Exchange
signed contracts with 30 listed companies, Tu said China's two
stock exchanges, in Shanghai and Shenzhen, have gone up 10 percent
and 2 percent respectively, despite the downturn of markets in
neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the healthy development of China's stock market
to high growth and low inflation, and said the securities
management departments have also promulgated a series of measures
to boost the stock market.
</P>
<P>
Since the latter half of last year, a number of large
state-owned enterprises playing an important role in the national
economy have been listed on the exchanges, said Tu, adding that
the 30 companies listed this year are expected to realize returns
of 30 percent more than the average.
</P>
<P>
Referring to those securities investment funds which were
successively listed this year, Tu said they have raised funds
totaling 10 billion yuan (about 1.2 billion U.S. dollars), which
not only improved the investment structure, but also offered
support to the stock market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
