<HEADLINE> Fourth Flood Crest Passing Honghu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONGHU (HUBEI), August 9 (Xinhua) -- The fourth flood crest on
the Yangtze River is passing through Honghu City in central
China's Hubei Province, raising the water level to 34.63 meters by
20:00 hours today.
</P>
<P>
The water level has surpassed the record level of 31.17 meter
in 1954, a local flood control official told Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
At present, the Yangtze River water is as high as top of the
embankment in Longkou Township. The Yangtze River dyke stands
seven meter above the city.
</P>
<P>
The local government has abandoned 12 secondary dykes and moved
4,000 people to safe places. Local residents remain calm. 
</P>
