<HEADLINE> Iranian Parliament Speaker Blasts Taliban for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Majlis (Parliament)
Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq Nouri Sunday strongly lashed out at the
Afghan Taliban militia for capturing 11 Iranian diplomats in
northern Afghanistan, Tehran radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Majlis open session, Nouri expressed regret on
the issue, saying "we consider such an action as a hostile stance
against the Islamic Republic of Iran."
</P>
<P>
The Iranian diplomats were captured by the Taliban forces in
Mazari Sharif Saturday after they took over the city, the main
stronghold of the Northern Alliance headed by President
Burhanuddin Rabbani.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Foreign Ministry summoned Pakistani Ambassador to
Tehran Javid Husain, urging the Pakistani government and the
Taliban to ensure the safety of the Iranian diplomats and to
release them as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Nouri said that arresting diplomats is an "unjustifiable act
against the international laws," stressing that Iran hopes the
Taliban would put an end to such an act as quickly as possible.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the Iranian Foreign Ministry to take urgent
measures to free the Iranian diplomats.
</P>
<P>
Terming the Afghan civil war as one of the serious concerns of
Iran and the Islamic world, he stated that peace and tranquillity
could only be restored in Afghanistan by means of unity and
cooperation and without foreign intervention.
</P>
<P>
The speaker expressed the hope that the Afghan belligerent
parties could find a way to end the bloodshed in the war-torn
country. 
</P>
