<HEADLINE> Yangtze Water Level at Shashi Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHASHI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- By 7:00 pm this evening, the water
level of the Yangtze River at Shashi City had dropped to 44.65
meters from this year's record level of 44.95 meters set at 4:00
am yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The water level is now below the level recorded during the
flood diversion in 1954, an official of the Shashi Hydrometric
Station said today.
</P>
<P>
The water velocity has slowed from 47,100 cubic meters per
second, recorded at 1:00 am today, to 45,900 cubic meters per second
at present.
</P>
<P>
The falling water level was attributed to the abandonment of some
secondary dikes, including one at Jianli County which was destroyed
at 12:00 am today, and the passing of the fourth flood crest, the
official said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
