<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- No flood-related casualties have
been reported in east China's Anhui Province, though water levels
of the Yangtze River in the province have surpassed the warning
levels at all measuring points and nearly 20,000 hectares of
farmland have been flooded.
</P>
<P>
As of August 8, 228,000 people had been evacuated, and no major
incidence of epidemics had been reported.
</P>
<P>
Local governments have allocated over 68 million yuan and
mobilized 3,200 vehicles and 2,500 vessels for rescue operations.
</P>
<P>
Over 700 medical teams also have been sent to affected areas
and medicines are being distributed to prevent any possible
outbreak of disease. 
