<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U-Shape Cofferdam on Yangtze River Formed in Jiujiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JIUJIANG, August 9 (Xinhua) -- A 90-meter-long U-shape
cofferdam formed with eight sunken boats has been completed at
18:18 hours today at the Jiujiang section of the raging Yangtze
River, a local flood control official said.
</P>
<P>
The cofferdam was designed to stop the raging Yangtze River
floodwaters from flowing into the city of Jiujiang through a
breach on the river dyke burst at 13:10 hours Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Yangtze River floodwaters are the worst since 1954.
</P>
<P>
The sunken boats are full of rock, rice, soybeans and whatever
materials at hand, said Liu Yizhong, an official of the Jiujiang
City Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
However, the boat-cofferdam is not completely sealed and some
floodwaters may still leak in from under the boats in some places,
he said, adding that efforts are continuing to plug all the leaks
completely.  
</P>
</TEXT>
