<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-09 12:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Launches Extensive Efforts to Rescue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Iran is launching extensive
efforts to rescue 11 Iranian diplomats captured by the Afghan
Taliban militia in northern Afghanistan, a senior Iranian Foreign
Ministry official announced Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Tehran radio, Iran's special envoy on
Afghan affairs Alaeddin Boroujerdi said that Iran had contacted
the Pakistani government, the United Nations as well as the
Taliban militia soon after the diplomats were captured Saturday
after Taliban forces took over Mazari Sharif in northern
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Boroujerdi said that the Iranian Ambassador to Pakistan had met
with top Pakistani officials, urging Islamabad to help secure the
release of the Iranian diplomats.
</P>
<P>
In Tehran, the Foreign Ministry summoned Pakistani Ambassador
to Iran Javid Husain Saturday night to demand the Pakistani
government assume responsibility for the safety of the Iranian
diplomats.
</P>
<P>
Iranian officials have contacted with some officials of the
Taliban forces over the issue, Boroujerdi said.
</P>
<P>
He added that efforts had also been made to seek help from the
International Committee of Red Cross and the U.N. Secretary
General's special envoy on Afghan affairs.
</P>
<P>
The 11 Iranian diplomats were captured by the Taliban forces
Saturday after they conquered Mazari Sharif, the main stronghold
of the Northern Alliance headed by Afghan President Burhanuddin
Rabbani, who was ousted by the Taliban in September 1996.
</P>
<P>
Boroujerdi refuted the claim by some Taliban officials in media
interviews that there were no Iranian diplomats when the Taliban
forces took over the Iranian consulate in Mazari Sharif.
</P>
<P>
"Undoubtedly, this claim was a mere lie," the Iranian
special envoy said.
</P>
<P>
He accused the Taliban militia of breaching the international
laws by breaking into the Iranian consulate and detaining the
Iranian diplomats, who were later transferred to an unknown
place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
