<HEADLINE> Philippine President Orders Intensifying of Flood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada Sunday ordered the Department of Public Works and Highways
and local government units to intensify their flood control drive
in preparation for the rainy days.
</P>
<P>
According to a press statement issued by the presidential
office, Estrada said flood control measures such as declogging of
drainage canals must be completed soon in view of the threats of
severe flooding as a result of the so-called La Nina weather
phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
Citing the severe floods that have hit China, Australia and
South Korea in the past few days, Estrada urged the full
cooperation of local government officials in the flood control
program.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said the devastating floods in the three countries have
shown that the dangers posed by La Nina are "very real" and must
be addressed properly by the concerned agencies of the government.
 
</P>
