<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Japanese Foreign Minister (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIDAIHE, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Since Japan is one of the major
developed countries in the world, China is willing to see Japanese
Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi's new cabinet make progress in
restoring its economy and mitigating economic difficulties in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin made the remarks today in a
meeting with Japanese Foreign Minister Masahiko Komura.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the East Asian financial crisis, which occurred
last year, has affected both China and Japan. He noted that China,
proceeding from stablizing the regional economy, has kept stable
the Chinese currency and has consequently paid price.
</P>
<P>
Komura briefed Jiang on the measures the new Japanese cabinet
has taken to stablize the Japanese economy. He said that Japan
will work hard to restore its economic development, and it will
make contributions to easing the Asian economic difficulty.
</P>
