<HEADLINE> U.S. Experts Fly into Nairobi to Probe Bomb Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Around 50 experts from Federal
Bureau of Investigation (FBI) of the United States are due in
Nairobi Sunday from Washington to further probe into the blast in
the Kenyan capital.
</P>
<P>
The bombing claimed at least 132 lives including 11 Americans,
and injured more than 4,200 people, 15 of them Americans.
</P>
<P>
Some FBI experts already flew into the Kenyan capital from
South Africa earlier Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Kenya Broadcast Corporation (KBC) said that a
group, self-declared the Islamic Army for the Liberation of
Moslem Holysites, had claimed to be responsible for the bomb
attack.
</P>
<P>
