<HEADLINE> Turkey Condemns Bomb Attacks in Kenya, Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel has strongly condemned two recent bomb attacks aimed at
American embassies in Kenya and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued late Saturday night by the Foreign Ministry
said that Demirel has sent messages to Bill Clinton, Daniel Arap
Moi and Benjamin Mkapa, presidents of the United States, Kenya and
Tanzania, expressing shock at the blasts.
</P>
<P>
Two powerful explosions occurred Friday near the U.S.
embassies in Nairobi and Dar es Salaam, leaving more than 140
people dead and over 1,000 others injured.
</P>
<P>
The statement said Turkey strongly condemns all kinds of
terrorism, adding that the latest atrocity has confirmed Turkey's
view that terrorism can be stopped only through international
cooperation as every country may be a target of terrorism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
