<HEADLINE> 18 Killed, 23 Injured in Turkey's Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen people were killed and 23
others injured early Sunday when several vehicles collided in
southeastern Turkey, the Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said the accident took place at 04:30 local time
(0130 GMT) when a minibus carrying workers collided with a truck
on the opposite side of the Adana-Ankara highway near Bestepeler
in Nigde Province, 350 kilometers southeast of the capital.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the incident, another minibus crashed into a
vehicle, which was stopped suddenly by the accident, and
turned over.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen people were killed at the scene and three others died
in a hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
