<HEADLINE> Poland Forecasts Bumper Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The Polish Central Bureau for
Statistics has forecast that the country's grain output this year
will exceed that of last year, the Gazeta Wyborcza newspaper
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said in its forecast that the grain output will
total between 26.6 million to 27 million tons, or 1.3 million to
1.7 million tons more than 1997. Of the grain output, wheat will
be about 9.3 million tons, up 1.1 million tons over last year.
</P>
<P>
The output of rapeseed will also see a jump of 68.9 percent to
1 million tons, up 400,000 tons over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The vegetable output is expected to be 5.3 million tons, up 7.8
percent over last year. But the fruit output suffered a 13.2
percent drop from last year.
</P>
<P>
Better cultivation and management by farmers and favorable
weather have led to increased grain yield per unit area, Polish
agricultural experts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
