<HEADLINE> Equities Decline on BSE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Equities turned weak showing
hefty falls in the indices on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE)
market during the past week on selling pressure due to exchanges
of fire along the borders in north Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
The BSE sensitive index dropped by 149.06 points to end the
week at 3062.25 as against last weekend close of 3211.31. The
national index also slid by 51.82 points to 1364.85 from the
previous weekend close of 1416.67. The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar
indexes were quoted substantially down at 315.84 and 123.58 at the
weekend compared with last weekend closes of 324.54 and 126.96
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The volume of business on BSE market was very low at 38.87
billion rupees (925.48 million U.S. dollars) as compared to last
week's turnover of 50.18 billion rupees (1.19 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The political uncertainty and economic difficulties both at
home and in Southeast Asia are the main reasons for the fall of
equities on BSE during the week, traders said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
