<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pierce Beats Hingis in Toshiba Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Martina Hingis of
Switzerland was beaten in straight sets by Mary Pierce of France
in the semifinal of the 450,000 US dollars Toshiba Tennis Classic
in San Diego, the United States on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Lindsay Davenport of the United States advanced to
her second straight WTA Tour final by beating fourth seed
compatroit Monica Seles 6-4, 2-6, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, who was looking to reach her first singles final in
three months, lost to Pierce 7-6 (9-7), 6-2. It was a sweet
revenge for Pierce who was beaten by the world number one in last
year's Australian Open final.
</P>
<P>
Hingis lost in the semifinals at both the French Open and
Wimbledon. Two weeks ago, she posted two victories in her home
country, helping Switzerland advance to the Fed Cup final.
</P>
<P>
Davenport will face Pierce in the final on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
After an exchange of breaks in the third set, Davenport broke
Seles in the 11th game on a backhand crosscourt winner. Seles
saved one match point in the next game, but lost the next to give
Davenport her first victory in three tries against the former
top-ranked player.
</P>
<P>
Seles, a two-time finalist, has been troubled by back spasms
throughout the week. The 22-year-old Davenport, ranked second in
the world, won her second singles title of the year at last week's
Bank of the West Classic in Stanford, California. Her other title
came in February at the Pan Pacific Open in Tokey, where she beat
Hingis in the final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
