<HEADLINE> Liberty Beats Sparks in WNBA Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The New York Liberty increased
its chance of qualifying for the playoff round by beating the Los
Angeles Sparks 80-62 in a WNBA game in New York Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Rebecca Lobo shone in the game with 22 points, her season-high
effort. She scored 19 points in the first half, netting 10-for-18
from the field plus eight rebounds.
</P>
<P>
It was the ninth time in 11 games New York won at Madison
Square Garden. Vickie Johnson and Sophia Witherspoon each
contributed 12 points for the winning side, which trail
conference-leading Charlotte by two games with five to play. New
York currently holds the final WNBA playoff spot.
</P>
<P>
It was the worst defeat this season for Los Angeles, which has
virtually lost its playoff chances with 10 wins and 15 losses.
</P>
<P>
Penny Toler was the top scorer for the Sparks with 14
points,followed by Lisa Leslie and Pamela McGee, each with 12.
</P>
<P>
In the other two games, the Cleveland Rockers beat the
Charlotte Sting 65-58 while the Phoenix Mercury downed the Utah S
tarzz 68-62. 
</P>
