</P>
<P>
STOCKHOLM -- The value of the Swedish currency krona has fallen
by more than 5 percent against the German mark in the last three
months, sparking belief that the seemingly far-away Asian
financial turmoil is affecting the Nordic country.
</P>
<P>
With the Stockholm Stock Exchange's downturn this summer, some
analysts suspect that foreign investors, who have sold off large
holdings of Swedish equities, turned their profits into foreign
currencies, which has created pressure on the krona.
</P>
<P>
The latest weakening of the krona started after Swedish
telecommunication giant Ericsson's interim report was made public,
while pharmaceutical company Astra's report intensified the
slide. (Sweden-Currency)
</P>
