<DOCNO> XIE19980809.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiujiang's Efforts to Plug Up Breach of Yangtze Dyke Slow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JIUJIANG, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Local people including soliders
are working strenuously in Jiujiang City, east China's Jiangxi
Province, to plug up a 60 m-breach on the city embankment of the
Yangtze River, but the effort has been slow due to technical
problems.
</P>
<P>
A section of the city dyke burst at 13:10 on Friday as rampant
floods, the worst since 1954, kept surging in the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
However, there had been no reported casualties so far in the
breach, according to Governor Shu Shengyou.
</P>
<P>
By now, people have sunk eight boats and dumped truckloads of
rock, paddy, soybeans and whatever at hand into the breach, in
case of a severe shortage of filling materials.
</P>
<P>
The effort has also been hampered due to a lack of experience
and equipment. A team of army experts have been summoned in from
Hebei Province, north China, to help Jiujiang plug up the
breach, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The army experts have decided to hammer in dozens of steel pipes
in three rows into the breached dyke, while a 90 m-cofferdam has
been built next to the breach to slow the flow of the raging
floodwater.
</P>
<P>
The whole operation may take another 24 hours, according to
army experts. "The previous dumping of boats and other materials
has slowed down the water flow by one third and laid a good
foundation for our operation," said an expert.
</P>
<P>
People have built a second cofferdam to prevent a four
sq. km. flooded urban area in the western part of the
city from further expanding. Currently, a third coffer dam, 3,000
m long, is being built to protect the eastern part of the city.
</P>
<P>
Since the burst occurred, thousands of residents have been
resettled and the city government has asked those living on floor
to move to higher floors.
</P>
<P>
So far, supplies of running water, electricity and daily
necessities have been adequate as usual in the city.
</P>
<P>
The city proper of Jiujiang, an industrial center and tourist
attraction in the middle reaches of the Yangtze with an
urban population of about 500,000, has an area of about 30 sq km.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
