<HEADLINE> Swedish Currency Weakens in Wake of Asian Financial Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The value of the Swedish
currency krona has fallen by more than 5 percent against the
German mark in the last three months, sparking belief that the
seemingly far-away Asian financial turmoil is affecting the Nordic
country.
</P>
<P>
With the Stockholm Stock Exchange's downturn this summer, some
analysts suspect that foreign investors, who have sold off large
holdings of Swedish equities, turned their profits into foreign
currencies, which has created pressure on the krona.
</P>
<P>
The latest weakening of the krona started after Swedish
telecommunication giant Ericsson's interim report was made public,
while pharmaceutical company Astra's report intensified the slide.
</P>
<P>
An economist of the Swedish Handelsbanken Markets said the
country's currency may also have been adversely affected by the
Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
"When there is turbulence in Asia, some investors lump together
Sweden with commodity-sensitive economies like Canada and
Australia. They then sell off Swedish krona together with Canadian
and Australian dollars," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
