<HEADLINE> China Has 11,695 km of Electrified Railways in Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- The electrification of
Beijing-Zhengzhou section of the north-south Beijing-Guangzhou trunk
railway line was completed and put into operation Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
It brings China's mileage of electrified railway lines in
operation to 11,695 km, said today's "People's Daily".
</P>
<P>
The electrification of the 695-km Beijing-Zhengzhou Railway
started in 1992 and cost 3.49 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Advanced technologies and equipment were used in haulage power
transmission, contact network, telecommunications and signals for
electrification of the Beijing-Zhengzhou Railway, which was
undertaken by the Electrification Engineering Bureau under the
Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
Facilities constructed during the electrification included
building of power transmission infrastructure, 16 haulage power
transmission stations, eight power stations, 500 km of power
transmission lines.
</P>
<P>
Before this, the 536 km section from Zhengzhou to Wuhan of the
2,300-km Beijing-Guangzhou Railway was electrified and put
into traffic in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Construction workers have now been busy electrifying the
remaining 1,069-km Wuhan-Guangzhou section, said the newspaper.
</P>
</TEXT>
