<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Basket of Crudes Price Drops Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan basket of crudes
and refined products closed the week with an average price of
10.15 dollars per barrel, which means a new drop of 26 dollar
cents, compared to last week's 10.41 dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Energy and Mines Ministry figures show that the average
price of the Venezuelan oil basket was 11.23 dollars per barrel
during the first half of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The average for the first seven months of this year is 11.10
dollars, which is 5.22 dollars lower than the average 16.32
dollars in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The average price of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries (OPEC) seven crude basket was 12.01 dollars per barrel
at the close of this week, which means a drop of 49 cents from the
previous week.
</P>
<P>
All these show that oil prices keep a dropping trend despite
the efforts made to cut production since July 1 by the OPEC member
and non-member countries, which by now produce more than 3.125
million barrels a day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
