recovered to win a crucial break point to even the score at 3-3.
</P>
<P>
From then on, Fromberg kept up the pressure to break Kucera
again and ran out a 6-4 winner.
</P>
<P>
In the Norman-Zabaleta match, the score was tied at 5-5 in the
first set and Norman squandered several chances to take the lead
before breaking for 6-5.
</P>
<P>
A lengthy game was stopped when Norman had problems triggered
by the heat, and a doctor came on court to measure his blood
pressure before his return to the court.
</P>
<P>
Norman served out to win the first set 7-5, and then finished
off the match with a 6-4 win in the second set. 
