<HEADLINE> Nicaragua Carry out Operation Against Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Nicaraguan authorities have
mobilized more than 1,500 policemen and army troops in an
operation to put down armed bands in the northern mountains, an
official report said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said armed bandits were responsible for the
violence in Matagalpa and Jinotega departments which had so far
killed 37 people. Robberies, extortions and kidnappings were also
rife in the region.
</P>
<P>
Three armed bands were dismembered as a result of the operation.
</P>
<P>
The report said the police captured 28 armed bandits last
Thursday and seized a military arsenal. 
