<HEADLINE> Stopping Rampant Oil Smuggling In South China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Customs officers in this capital
of south China's Guangdong Province have dealt a serious blow to oil
traffickers on the Pearl River Delta during the current fight
against smuggling.
</P>
<P>
During June, 11 oil smuggling cases were stopped and more
than 12,000 tons of refined oil seized. In 9 of the cases, 20
million yuan worth of diesel oil was seized.
</P>
<P>
After the crackdown on maritime oil smuggling, there
have been an increased number of fishing boats and small vessels
involved in the illegal business. So, Customs officers are
increasing surveillance on the river estuary.
</P>
<P>
