<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Exports to Africa Soar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese exports to African
countries soared in the first half of this year and the momentum
is expected to be maintained for the next six months, according to
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
According to Chinese Customs statistics, exports to Africa from
January to June hit 1.99 billion U.S. dollars, soaring 44.1
percent from the the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, China's total exports rose 7.6 percent
from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The impressive export growth mainly stemmed from China's market
diversification efforts, said Fu Zhengluo, a researcher with the
Chinese Academy of International Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China's market diversification strategy was implemented in
1990. It aims to expand trade with Africa and Latin America, which
have been comparatively unexplored markets for Chinese traders.
</P>
<P>
The country's traditional export markets are the Asian,
European and North American countries.
</P>
<P>
Efforts to expand Chinese traders' share in the African and
Latin American markets have paid off, Fu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980809.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Power Grids to Be Upgraded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 9 (Xinhua) -- China plans to invest around 100
billion yuan to upgrade its urban power grids over the next three
years, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Improving urban grids will expand power supply capacity and
enhance the quality of life of residents, said Wei Guangyao,
director of the Safety Operation Department under the State Power
Corp of China (SP).
</P>
<P>
The program is expected to play an active role in promoting the
domestic machinery and electronic industry, because almost all the
equipment needed in the upgrading project will be purchased from at
home.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, it is destined to create huge demand for
air-conditioners, electric water heaters and other home
electrical appliances, Wei said.
</P>
<P>
The ambitious plan will also create numerous jobs, which are
vital in view of the growing number of laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
After careful research, the SP has produced a blueprint to upgrade
the power grids in 280 large and medium-sized cities by 2000. The
project gets under way in the first 62 cities this year.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that about 30 billion yuan will be put in the
project every year in the 1998-2000 period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980809.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-09 </DATE_TIME>
