<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Reinforcing Embankments Along River, Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 9 (Xinhua) -- While the provinces in the
middle reaches of the Yangtze are fighting a serious battle
against the worst flooding since 1954, the city of Shanghai, which
lies at the river's mouth, has increased spending on local flood
control facilities.
</P>
<P>
So far, 244 million yuan has been spent dredging river channels
and building or rebuilding embankments, flood gates and pumping
stations.
</P>
<P>
People from local flood control departments have been taking a
close look at all the major facilities in the city and some
anti-flood exercises have been carried out in the Pudong
New Area and on Chongming Island.
</P>
<P>
Though three flood crests have passed the city without
incident this summer, local officials worry that flooding, as well
as typhoons or tides, could still damage the city.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, calamities like these caused 524 breaches in local
dykes and destroyed 7 flood gates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
