<HEADLINE> Chile Condemns Bomb Attacks on U.S. Embassies in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Chile strongly condemned the
terrorist bombing attacks on the U.S. embassies in Nairobi and Dar
Es Salaam, the La Nacion newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Affairs Ministry, in a statement, reiterated its
rejection to any kind of terrorist action, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the actions deserve universal
condemnation and all countries should give support to capturing
the intellectual and material authors of these deplorable
incidents.
</P>
<P>
It said that President Eduardo Frei has sent to the governments
of Kenya, Tanzania and the United States "its deepest feelings of
regret and solidarity for the deaths of citizens of their
countries as a consequence of these acts of terror and violence.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean government ordered to reinforce police protection
to the United States embassy in Santiago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
