<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Beats US to Face Yugoslavia in Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Russian cagers outwitted their
American peers 66-64 in a fierce semifinal, clinching their spot
in the final at the World Basketball Championship here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Russia thus will vie for the gold medal against Yugoslavia who
outscored the host Greece 78-73 in overtime in other semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Russia staged a late rally, coming back from 10 points down to
win the battle as Sergey Panov scored the winning layup with 4
seconds left.
</P>
<P>
American Wendell Alexis desperately threw in a 30-foot shot but
only after the final buzzer.
</P>
<P>
The United States, which went scoreless for the final 3:08,
will play Greece for third place Sunday. A loss would mean the
first worlds without a medal for the Americans in 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Dejan Bodiroga had 31 points and Zeljko Rebraca added 20 points
and 13 rebounds for Yugoslavia, who overcame a 12-point deficit in
the second half.
</P>
<P>
The European champion, silver medalist at the 1996 Olympics, is aiming for a
record fourth title.
</P>
<P>
Backed by a capacity crowd of 18,000 at Olympic arena, Greece
opened up its biggest lead at 48-36 with 11:00 remaining.
</P>
<P>
But Yugoslavia clawed back thanks to some poor foul shooting by
Greece, which finished 11-for-22 from the line.
</P>
<P>
A layup by Aleksandar Djordjevic put Yugoslavia ahead 57-56
with 1:40 left in regulation. Greece's Nikos Economou who scored
team-high 25 points, hit one of two free throws 23 seconds later
to tie the game and send it to overtime.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia opened the extra period with a 9-2 run, capped by a
Bodiroga jumper, and held on for its 16th straight victory over
the Greeks, dating to 1987.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Sergey Babkov had a game-high 30 points in just 24
minutes, including back-to-back 3-pointers that tied the game,
64-64, with 1:23 remaining. Vassily Karassev added 10 points.
</P>
<P>
The loss to Russia means the United States will have to go
through qualifying for a spot in the 2000 Sydney Olympics. Only
the world champion and host Australia earn automatic berths.
</P>
<P>
In the games to determine fifth through eighth places, Italy
defeated Lithuania 76-71, while Spain beat Argentina 77-64.
</P>
<P>
Australia edged Brazil 79-75 to take ninth place and Puerto
Rico beat Canada 92-81 for 11th. 
</P>
</TEXT>
