<HEADLINE> Hepatitis B Outbreak Causes Alarm in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Costa Rican Health Ministry
keeps alert about a hepatitis-B outbreak in the Bijagua Community,
near the border with Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
Data released Saturday by the ministry show 69 cases of
hepatitis-B have been reported in the area, marking the first mass
outbreak of the disease in the country.
</P>
<P>
The main symptoms of the disease are high fever, skin
yellowing, change of color in urine. If untreated it can give way
to liver cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
