<HEADLINE> Rafter Enters Final of Du Maurier Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Third-seeded Patrick Rafter of
Australia advanced to the final of the Du Maurier Open tennis by
defeating Briton Tim Henman 6-2, 6-4 in Toronto on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He will face either Andre Agassi of the United States or
Richard Krajicek of the Netherlands for the championship on Sunday
as the latters will play their semifinal later Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, the world's fifth-ranked player has advanced through
the tournament with straight-set wins over fellow Aussie
14th-seeded Mark Philippoussis, fifth-seeded Jonas Bjorkman of
Sweden and seventh-seeded Henman.
</P>
<P>
"He played a great match, he never let me get into it," Henman
said, "It's more him playing a very good match than me doing
anything wrong."
</P>
<P>
Rafter took just over an hour to beat Henman with near flawless
tennis. Henman had 23 unforced errors while Rafter finished with
12.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, 25, has steadily improved his game in the last two
years. He finished the 1996 season ranked 62nd, but a year later
jumped to the second spot in the world behind Pete Sampras after
winning the 1997 U.S. Open. 
</P>
</TEXT>
